cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with tracking objects in image sequences. The use of Bayesian filtering and Monte Carlo methods suggests that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category, as these techniques are commonly used in robot localization and mapping. The paper also involves the estimation of importance proposal probabilities, which is a common problem in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of image sequences, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
